  "prompt": "Can you get pregnant without cervical mucus?",
  "response": "Cervical mucus plays an important role in fertility by helping sperm reach and fertilize an egg. However, the absence of noticeable cervical mucus does not necessarily mean you cannot conceive. Some women's cervical mucus is less noticeable or may not change in a way that's easily detectable. \n\nFactors such as hydration levels, diet, and hormonal changes can affect cervical mucus production. If you're trying to conceive and concerned about your cervical mucus, it might be helpful to consult with a healthcare provider or a fertility specialist. They can provide guidance and may suggest methods to improve cervical mucus production or alternative approaches to tracking ovulation.",
